# Makefile.secureos — TinyCC source file list for the SecureOS freestanding
# in-OS compiler.
#
# STATUS: SCAFFOLD (Phase 1). This file enumerates the libtcc sources needed
# for an x86_64 ELF-emitting compiler and records the porting notes. It is
# NOT yet wired into a working build — that is Phases 3-4 of
# plans/2026-05-28-in-os-toolchain-self-hosting.md. Listing the files now
# keeps the vendor surface auditable and gives the execute issue a concrete
# starting point (mirrors vendor/bearssl/Makefile.secureos).
#
# Target: x86_64, ELF output, hosted-on-SecureOS (compiler runs in-OS).

# --- libtcc core (compiler API, preprocessor, codegen front, ELF/link) ---
# These are target-independent and always required.
TCC_CORE_SRCS = \
  libtcc.c \
  tccpp.c \
  tccgen.c \
  tccelf.c \
  tccasm.c \
  tccdbg.c

# --- x86_64 backend (codegen + relocations + the shared x86 assembler) ---
TCC_TARGET_SRCS = \
  x86_64-gen.c \
  x86_64-link.c \
  i386-asm.c

# --- All sources for the in-OS libtcc ---
# tccrun.c (-run / JIT), tcctools.c (ar/makedef), tcc.c (CLI main),
# tccpe.c / tccmacho.c / tcccoff.c (non-ELF object formats), and every
# non-x86_64 backend are intentionally EXCLUDED: the in-OS compiler only
# needs file-output ELF for the host arch. The SecureOS `cc` driver under
# user/apps/cc/ provides its own main() and calls the libtcc API directly.
TCC_ALL_SRCS = \
  $(TCC_CORE_SRCS) \
  $(TCC_TARGET_SRCS)

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Porting notes (the actual Phase 3 work)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# TinyCC assumes a hosted environment. To build it freestanding against the
# SecureOS userland C library (user/libs/clib, Phase 2) the execute issue must:
#
#  1. Provide a config: define TCC_TARGET_X86_64 and TCC_TARGET_ELF; undefine
#     CONFIG_TCC_BACKTRACE, CONFIG_TCC_BCHECK, and the -run/JIT path so
#     tccrun.c is not pulled in. Set ONE_SOURCE=0 (compile units separately).
#
#     Phase 2 (issue #408 sub-slice): the config macros for this step are
#     pinned in `vendor/tinycc/config-secureos.h` and verified by the host
#     gate `tinycc_config_secureos` (build/scripts/test_tinycc_config_secureos.sh).
#     Phase 3 should pass `-include vendor/tinycc/config-secureos.h` (or
#     symlink it as `vendor/tinycc/tinycc/config.h` from the build tree)
#     rather than re-deriving these knobs.
#
#  2. Satisfy libtcc's libc dependencies from user/libs/clib: malloc/free/
#     realloc, qsort, setjmp/longjmp, the str*/mem* family, and stdio over
#     os_fs_* (fopen/fread/fwrite/fclose/fprintf). TinyCC's error path uses
#     setjmp/longjmp, so that pair must be real, not stubs.
#
#  3. Replace TinyCC's filesystem and "find include/library" logic with the
#     SecureOS VFS paths (sysincludes default to /apps/dev/include).
#
#  4. Pin the produced ELF to the SecureOS user image base / entry convention
#     so the SOF packer (user/libs/sofpack) can wrap it and the launcher can
#     load it. The output is then handed to sofpack, not written as raw ELF.
#
#  5. Measure peak compile-time memory for the sample translation units and
#     record the per-app arena size the `cc` manifest must request (Phase 1
#     made the arena size a free knob; this step picks the value).
